      {
        "id": 2211657,
        "name": "John Fagan",
        "username": "John_Fagan",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/john_fagan/{size}/1187_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-01T20:07:47.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2075015&amp;iNote=6442125\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2012 Mount Eden Vineyards Chardonnay Santa Cruz Mountains</strong></a> <em>- USA, California, San Francisco Bay, Santa Cruz Mountains (6/30/2017)</em><br>\nCoravin\u2019d and I dove right in. Lighter color than typical for MEV. More yellow than gold. The nose leads with sexy, toasty oak. Next comes the citrus, lemon grass, ginger, fresh sweet herbs. You name it; this has everything aromatically that you long for in a great young Chardonnay. The palate is fresh and bright but not at all firm or too primary. The oak now moves to 2nd fiddle as the citrus, lemon meringue flavors are joined by some stone fruits. The long lasting palate impression (finish) is fresh and delightful. I find this to be more generous than some other recent tasters but from my experience, I know this will continue to develop positively for a decade. If you own a case, no reason not to introduce yourself. I just did. 94pts. Arguably the prettiest Chardonnay I\u2019ve had in quite a while. Drink 2019-2029. <em><strong>(94 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" class=\"broken-image\" title=\"This image is broken\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-unlink svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#unlink\"></use></svg></span></p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
